I ordered here on Grubhub. The delivery time was very quick, but I also live nearby. I got the steak and chicken sandwich, with greens and potato chips. I was disappointed that the platter was so messy because all 3 items were in the same plate. They didn’t cut my sandwich in half so by the time I did, it was falling to pieces. The dressing on my salad was all over the chips and sandwich which I didn’t prefer. Everything was drenched. The meats were Nice and tender, but it was masked bc they used way too much garlic aioli. Sometimes less is best. Overall I still enjoyed the meal as a whole but the presentation could have been better.

Really cute spot with good food, great Wi-Fi, and lots of power outlets. The staff was super kind and helpful, so shout out to them for sure. It's also a really cute shop that lets a lot of daylight in. Knocking off 1 star only bc 1) the music was repetitive and loud enough to eventually wear on you and 2) they still use straws. I could have helped with #1 by asking for a switchup so that's my bad. For #2, let's definitely move away from straws and focus on recycled, biodegradable materials!

Pretty much a fancy bodega/coffee shop . They have ample seating some good healthy items on the menu in a health food desert and the coffee is strong. BUT minus three stars for service. I asked if they had gluten free bread because I’m allergic and the guy said to me they were out of it, then added “isn’t that just in your head?” He then kept trying to push a veggie burger on me but couldn’t tell me ingredients. Health department be warned! I met the owner next time and he told me they actually don’t carry any gluten free bread and don’t have options for someone who is intolerant like me. Next time I went, I asked for a salad to stay and it was packaged up to go. Not sure what’s going on with this place but for the price of items on the menu, I hope they get it together.

Just visited this spot today with some friends to try something new for breakfast and so sorry I did. Ordered a cappuccino with skim milk and when I brought it back to my seat I thought it smelled strange and tasted odd. When I went back to the counter to let them know I was concerned about the milk, I was treated as if I was trying to cheat them and get a free drink. One woman behind the counter ordered her co-worker to sip the milk they used and they said it was fine, and tried to make me pay for a brand new drink. I told them it didn’t seem fair, as I didn’t even drink this one and was clearly not trying to pull any scheme on them and she just told me she’s not allowed to give me any free giveaways, since she has given others the same milk in drinks and no one else had complained. After looking for a relaxing breakfast with friends I was left feeling very uncomfortable by such unnecessary rude and cold distrust. I will not be returning.
